This paper is primarily focused on network security and attack modeling, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of planners and algorithms for automating the generation and execution of attack paths, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The implementation of the attack model and integration with a penetration testing tool involves software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the approach, which is relevant to network infrastructure (cs.NI).
